Distribution and habitat:
—It should be noted that both of these new species overlap in their distributions in the 
Cape
region’s mountains, specifically in the northern portion, an area called the Sierra de La Victoria (
23.602°N
). Both species are less common in the Cape’s southern mountains (Sierra San Lázaro, 
23.252°N
). However, in the eastern portion (slopes toward the Gulf of 
California
) both species populations are more common than in the western slopes of the Pacific, where they are infrequent (see 
Figure 1
).
